    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA56-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu varaiviṭai melivu āṟṟuvikkun tōḻikkut talaivi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said to the confidante who was encouraging [HER in her] weakness [until] the time of marriage.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA56">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kuṟunilaik kuraviṉ ciṟunaṉai naṟuvī</l>
<l>            vaṇṭutaru nāṟṟam vaḷikalan tīyak</l>
<l>            kaṇkaḷi peṟūuṅ kaviṉpeṟu kālai</l>
<l>            yelvaḷai ñekiḻttōrk kalla luṟīiyar</l>
<l>            ceṉṟa neñcañ ceyviṉaik kucāvā </l>
<l>            voruṅkuvara ṉacaiyoṭu varuntuṅ kollō</l>
<l>            varuḷā ṉātali ṉaḻintivaṇ vantu</l>
<l>            toṉṉala ṉiḻantaveṉ poṉṉiṟa nōkki</l>
<l>            yēti lāṭṭi yivaḷeṉap</l>
<l>            pōyiṉṟu kollō nōytalai maṇantē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>[My] heart, gone to make [him] unhappy</l>
<l rend="indent2">to the one who made loose [my] light bangles</l>
<l rend="indent">at a time that obtains beauty, when the eye obtains delight by</l>
<l rend="indent">trumpet-flower trees that mingled in the wind with the fragrance,</l>
<l rend="indent">attracting bees, of the small-budded fragrant blossoms of the</l>
<l rend="indent3">short-trunked Kura tree,</l>
<l>does it suffer with yearning of coming [back] together,</l>
<l rend="indent3">without inquiring after the work to be done?</l>
<l>Is it gone [for good], entangled with pain,</l>
<l rend="indent">desolate because he has not been considerate, coming [back] here,</l>
<l rend="indent">looking at my gold colour that that has lost [its] old goodness,</l>
<l rend="indent">saying “she is a stranger”?</l>
    </lg>
         </div>
